<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4990] Do not allow use of collection with compact storage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4990</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;You can define ColumnFamily with collection type and compact storage as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;CREATE TABLE test (
  user ascii PRIMARY KEY,
  mails list&amp;lt;text&amp;gt;
) WITH COMPACT STORAGE;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This does not make sense and end up error when inserting data to collection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;INSERT INTO test (user, mails) VALUES (&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;foo&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;foo@foo.org&apos;&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it is better not to allow defining such ColumnFamily.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
